WEBVTT

00:00.866 --> 00:04.090
a little boy wanted a bicycle, but he didn't know how to pray for one.

00:04.391 --> 00:12.161
So he was watching a television church program, and a very traditional service appeared on the screen, and he watched closely how the pastor prayed.

00:12.882 --> 00:28.562
So at the end of the day, he got near his bed, kneeled down, and he prayed, and he said this, Lord, most high, thou art great and majestic, and if it is in thy sovereign will and in thy eternal plan, that I can get myself a bicycle in your time, and according to thy gracious will, would you

00:28.642 --> 00:31.285
Please get me a bicycle in Jesus name.

00:31.466 --> 00:31.926
I pray.

00:32.387 --> 00:32.687
Amen.

00:33.689 --> 00:37.153
Two days later there he was waiting and still no bicycle.

00:37.233 --> 00:39.656
So he began to think that he needed a different type of prayer.

00:39.696 --> 00:42.660
So he turned on the television again and he found a prosperity preacher.

00:43.161 --> 00:50.130
And so at the end of the day he got near his bed, nailed down and he prayed and he said this, Lord, I declare my need for a bicycle.

00:50.370 --> 01:00.380
And I declare and claim a nice blue colored bicycle and delivered to my home within 24 hours, I believe, and lay claim to it in Jesus' name, amen.

01:01.601 --> 01:05.284
And again, after several days, no bicycle.

01:05.304 --> 01:14.013
And so one day as he was passing the hall in his home, he saw a statue of the Virgin Mary on the shelf and he took it, he walked outside of the home, came back, it wasn't there anymore.

01:14.774 --> 01:17.616
And later that night, he got down on his knees and he started to pray.

01:18.257 --> 01:19.378
And he began, he said,

01:19.458 --> 01:22.762
tear Jesus if you ever want to see your mother again.

01:22.782 --> 01:30.610
And you may laugh at that joke this morning and that story, but some of us, that's how a relationship to God may feel like.

01:31.591 --> 01:40.080
And today's name of God is actually one of the most misunderstood name that causes many people, disappointment, disillusionment, and discouragement.

01:41.041 --> 01:45.266
And today we're going to look at Jehovah Raffa, God our healer.

01:45.378 --> 01:58.470
And we may be like that little boy trying every prayer and every ritual and going to every pastor to pray and doing everything to convince God to heal us of our sickness and still not experiencing the healing we want.

01:59.251 --> 02:01.693
So this morning, let's look at this beautiful name of God.

02:02.014 --> 02:03.295
Let's begin with prayer.

02:04.876 --> 02:08.700
God, we thank you for this moment that we can gather and worship you.

02:08.760 --> 02:15.346
And Lord, look into your word because your word is a light and a lamp to our feet that we may walk in your truth.

02:15.618 --> 02:20.986
Speak to us, and may we hear and receive and obey what you've asked us to do.

02:21.667 --> 02:23.731
In Jesus' name we pray, amen.

02:24.993 --> 02:38.614
This morning's passage is found in Exodus chapter 15, verses 22 to 26, and here we find Israel had just crossed over the Red Sea, and they had gone through a remarkable miracle of God, and they were singing and celebrating and dancing for their newfound freedom.

02:39.375 --> 02:43.922
But immediately after their worshiping finish, they traveled about three days towards Mount Sinai,

02:44.290 --> 02:48.056
and only to find themselves thirsty and dry in parts looking for water.

02:48.817 --> 02:55.949
Now it's interesting to know that after great victories, very often, or even after worshipal moments, trials and temptations suddenly appear.

02:56.650 --> 02:59.856
So it's something definitely we should be aware of and prepare it for.

02:59.876 --> 03:08.770
1 Peter 4, verse 12 says, Dear friends, don't be surprised at the fiery trials you're going through as if something strange were happening to you.

03:09.371 --> 03:10.994
Instead, be very glad

03:11.074 --> 03:15.340
for these trials make you partakers with Christ in his suffering.

03:15.360 --> 03:23.952
Now, Peter is exhorting us not to think of the trials we're facing as something strange, but rather something that makes us partners with Christ in his suffering.

03:24.433 --> 03:26.856
So essentially, Peter is saying, one, don't be surprised.

03:27.237 --> 03:28.459
Two, be prepared.

03:28.779 --> 03:29.801
Three, accept it.

03:30.121 --> 03:32.645
And four, pray for unreasonable joy.

03:32.845 --> 03:34.808
Because of course, no trial is joyful.

03:35.289 --> 03:36.670
It's naturally joyful to go through.

03:37.131 --> 03:39.154
We need supernatural joy.

03:39.906 --> 03:48.460
Now the wilderness was not a place of plentiful water, but rather a place of blistering heat and sand dunes and sandstorms and sand serpents and parched lips.

03:49.101 --> 03:54.730
And so when Israel arrived at a place called Mara, they could not drink the water because it says it was bitter.

03:55.311 --> 04:01.101
And soon the singers and dancers and the voices that lifted up in praise and to God suddenly became silent.

04:01.241 --> 04:04.586
The voice of praise became the voice of complaint.

04:04.606 --> 04:06.930
They complained because there was no water at Mara.

04:07.074 --> 04:07.775
that they could drink.

04:07.815 --> 04:08.876
It was found with bitterness.

04:09.236 --> 04:13.500
They complained because they were in a discouraging situation and missed what they had in Egypt.

04:13.941 --> 04:19.926
They complained because it's part of our human nature to complain, especially when things don't work out the way we want them to.

04:20.327 --> 04:24.711
They complained because they realized their expectations far exceeded realities.

04:25.992 --> 04:36.562
When our spouse or our kids or our boss or our jobs or finance or health, our church, our pastors, leaders, our parents, siblings, friends, and I can go on and on and on, when they don't meet our expectations,

04:36.994 --> 04:38.116
we often complain.

04:38.957 --> 04:45.228
And so God was testing his people, not because he didn't know what was in their hearts, but because they didn't know what was in their hearts.

04:45.869 --> 05:01.034
Deuteronomy 8 verse 2 reads, remember how the Lord your God led you all the way in the wilderness for these 40 years to humble you and to test you in order to know what was in your heart, whether or not you would keep his commands.

05:01.735 --> 05:03.698
You know, people often say, well, I know what's in my heart.

05:04.258 --> 05:11.308
But they forget what Jeremiah 17 9 says that the heart is deceitful above all things and desperately wicked who can know it.

05:12.130 --> 05:19.340
Even Paul writes in 1 Thessalonians 2 verse 4, we are not trying to please people but God who tests our hearts.

05:20.021 --> 05:24.528
You see, the Lord tests us to encourage us towards spiritual growth, to bring out the best in us.

05:25.249 --> 05:34.002
The devil tempts us to bring the worst in out in us and to discourage us from spiritual growth, but rather create spiritual immaturity.

05:34.594 --> 05:40.541
See, the attitude that we take towards difficulty determines which direction our life will go.

05:40.581 --> 05:46.247
And for what life does to us depends on what life finds in us.

05:46.407 --> 05:47.148
Let me say that again.

05:47.509 --> 05:53.355
The attitude that we take towards difficulties determines which direction life will go.

05:53.415 --> 05:58.181
And what life does to us depends on what life finds in us.

05:58.721 --> 06:02.706
And so if we trust God and obey His word, we'll pass the tests of life and growth.

06:03.170 --> 06:09.717
But if through unbelief we complain and disobey the Lord, we're going to fail the test again and again and remain immature.

06:10.458 --> 06:16.605
That is why in this passage in Exodus we see something very interesting and we're going to look at later when God gives and reveals his name.

06:17.245 --> 06:25.014
Prior to that in Exodus 15, 25 it says, there he made a statute as he gives this promise and an ordinance for them and there he tested them.

06:26.275 --> 06:28.658
You see, complaining doesn't solve the problems of life.

06:29.186 --> 06:37.275
And if we try to run away from a difficult situation, we'll probably meet the same problems in a new place and still not be able to solve them.

06:38.537 --> 06:42.662
Because the heart of every problem is the problem of our heart.

06:43.603 --> 06:48.188
The heart of every problem that we face is actually rooted in the problem of our heart.

06:49.189 --> 06:52.954
I'd like to share a very important truth in how we relate to God.

06:52.974 --> 06:54.155
A man of God named A.W.

06:54.175 --> 06:56.818
Tozer in the book, The Knowledge of the Holy, he said this,

06:57.314 --> 07:01.499
What comes into our minds when we think about God is the most important thing about us.

07:02.300 --> 07:14.255
The most significant fact about any man or woman is not what he may at any given time may say or do, but what he deep in his heart conceives God to be like.

07:14.275 --> 07:18.520
So the question for us this morning is, what comes to your mind when you think about God?

07:19.782 --> 07:26.450
We all tend to create this image of God and of others by what we may hear about them or experience a life with them.

07:27.298 --> 07:38.294
And so this is something very important, is that we should not interpret God through our circumstances, rather interpret our circumstances through the goodness of God.

07:39.175 --> 07:54.898
Be careful not to interpret and understand and create an image of God based on what you and I are going through, our circumstances of life, whether good or bad, but rather interpret what you're going through, the circumstances of your life through the filter of God's goodness, his character, his love, and understand who he is.

07:55.234 --> 07:58.637
Because you can't control what happens to us, to you and to me.

07:59.238 --> 08:03.041
But you can control how you frame it and how you interpret it and how you perceive it.

08:03.822 --> 08:09.528
How we imagine and interpret God will determine our relationship with Him and will direct our future.

08:10.048 --> 08:20.218
That is why the names of God series that we've been going through this summer has been so helpful because it helps us to know the character and the nature of God because His name reveals that to us.

08:20.238 --> 08:24.402
Now even though Israel found water, they could not drink it because it was very bitter.

08:24.898 --> 08:30.726
which indicates it had become polluted, bacterial infected, and it probably stank with a foul odor.

08:31.487 --> 08:36.333
And though Israel complained, Moses cried out to God, and then God showed Moses a tree.

08:37.054 --> 08:40.379
And Moses cast that tree into the waters and it was made sweet.

08:40.999 --> 08:44.384
Now here's an interesting but also comforting truth to learn from this.

08:45.345 --> 08:49.431
Do you know that God already prepared the tree years before they arrived?

08:49.491 --> 08:51.954
Because the tree didn't just show up miraculously,

08:52.322 --> 08:54.806
It would have taken years for that tree to grow.

08:55.828 --> 09:01.737
So do you know that God is preparing things now for your future?

09:01.777 --> 09:05.904
And God has already prepared what you need today, years back.

09:06.746 --> 09:10.111
We just need to ask Him, receive it, and seek Him.

09:10.993 --> 09:13.417
Because God is a God that works, He prepares.

09:13.477 --> 09:19.186
And as we trust Him to lead us and guide us, we can find confidence in His faithfulness.

09:19.778 --> 09:25.948
Now the text does not tell us what kind of tree or the quality of the tree that caused the bitter water to become sweet.

09:26.569 --> 09:36.445
But some Jewish rabbinic literature that offers commentary and interpretation suggests that these writings, whatever kind of tree it was, says that wood was probably bitter.

09:37.307 --> 09:42.856
So God used bitter wood mixed with bitter water to make sweet water.

09:43.778 --> 09:46.482
Now it's a reminder to us that God doesn't work like us.

09:47.042 --> 09:47.923
And it doesn't make sense.

09:47.963 --> 09:50.386
In our understanding, bitter, mixed with bitter, should equal bitter.

09:51.126 --> 09:57.754
But with God, bitter wood, mixed with bitter water, results in clean drinking water.

09:57.774 --> 10:05.762
In verse 26 and forms is that after this miracle at Mara, God revealed Himself to Moses and the children of Israel as Jehovah Rafa.

10:06.243 --> 10:08.065
I am the Lord that heals you.

10:08.825 --> 10:12.990
God used the bitter water to teach His people a lesson that He is our healer.

10:13.831 --> 10:16.754
They would have died of thirst, but through this miracle, God

10:17.218 --> 10:19.841
heal them from certain death.

10:19.861 --> 10:24.746
In verse 26, we see God ties healing to walking in accordance with statutes and commandments.

10:25.066 --> 10:31.654
In verse 25, also just prior to that, we already read how God tested them by making the statute an ordinance.

10:31.674 --> 10:46.930
Then in verse 26, it says, if you diligently heed the voice of the Lord your God and do what is right in his sight and give year to his commandments and keep all the statutes, I will put none of the diseases on you which I brought on the Egyptians for I am the Lord who heals you.

10:47.554 --> 10:53.542
You see, the Egyptians didn't seek God, the one true God, rather they sought idols, resulting in the ten plagues.

10:54.523 --> 10:57.487
And so these four conditions we read, and then a promise.

10:58.048 --> 11:05.418
First is if you will diligently harken, it's literally saying if you will really listen to what I, your God, have to say.

11:06.099 --> 11:11.486
And do what is right in his eyes, which is naturally to say, do what he considers is right.

11:11.526 --> 11:14.610
Not what we consider is right, what he considers is right.

11:14.850 --> 11:17.334
Third, give heed to his commandments.

11:17.354 --> 11:19.877
Literally means pay attention to his commandments.

11:19.937 --> 11:26.887
And fourth, keep all the statues, guard all the statues, pay attention to what God is teaching us and do it.

11:27.808 --> 11:30.172
And the promise now is stated actually in negative terms.

11:30.312 --> 11:34.057
I will put none of the diseases upon you, which I brought upon the Egyptians.

11:34.097 --> 11:39.044
Literally, God is saying, all the sicknesses which I put on the Egyptians, I will not put on you.

11:40.006 --> 11:43.090
Here he's obviously referring to the plagues that

11:43.170 --> 11:49.598
came by God upon and afflicted the Egyptians, the 10 plagues that helped them to find deliverance from Egypt.

11:50.199 --> 11:53.623
Therefore, God is saying, I will not make you suffer as the Egyptians did.

11:54.444 --> 12:00.472
Now, God is not talking about the sicknesses that may come with old age and pollutants of the air and food.

12:01.253 --> 12:05.458
It's a sickness that comes from rebellion against his ways and his commandments.

12:05.954 --> 12:16.887
And perhaps the lesson that God is teaching his people in Marais is basically saying this, if you will follow my instructions, I will heal your bodies, your emotions, your relationships and circumstances.

12:17.568 --> 12:27.300
But if you choose to walk in the ways of the world, which is like Egypt, a place of bondage and captivity, then you will not be immune to the world's diseases.

12:28.161 --> 12:35.410
Now the essence of God's character as Jehovah Raffa is the Lord our healer is not a guarantee that we will never get sick or we will be immune

12:35.522 --> 12:36.143
from disease.

12:36.863 --> 12:39.706
Suffering invades and infects us in so many ways.

12:40.266 --> 12:52.878
Whether it's through pain or disease or failure, anxiety, disappointment, family breakdown and relational trauma, abuse and influence of demonic forces or death were all part of a dysfunctional world due to the effects of sin.

12:53.379 --> 12:58.443
Even creation is groaning and crying and longing for freedom and liberation.

12:59.244 --> 13:05.490
We read in scripture at times that God miraculously heals people or does some extraordinary event of liberation.

13:05.986 --> 13:10.212
So we may come to expect that it would happen every single time.

13:11.114 --> 13:11.955
So can God heal us?

13:12.916 --> 13:13.157
Yes.

13:13.978 --> 13:14.839
Will God heal us?

13:15.961 --> 13:16.221
Yes.

13:17.123 --> 13:20.968
And that is ultimately the result and the guarantee of the resurrection.

13:21.349 --> 13:27.218
The resurrection promises us complete healing, deliverance, freedom, and new life.

13:28.039 --> 13:30.983
However, will God heal us in this life now?

13:31.845 --> 13:35.410
The answer to that question is a matter of timing,

13:35.682 --> 13:36.283
purpose.

13:37.004 --> 13:38.146
And so it's actually a maybe.

13:39.147 --> 13:44.956
God may say at times yes and God may say no and at times God may say wait.

13:45.817 --> 13:49.042
Regardless of his answer we must accept his will.

13:49.062 --> 13:56.193
Ask God to use our pain, our weakness, our brokenness to bring him glory and to produce an unnatural joy in us.

13:57.394 --> 14:00.659
Some of you may beware and thank you for those who were where and were praying.

14:01.120 --> 14:05.266
You know last September I was pumping my daughter's bicycle and

14:05.346 --> 14:07.288
As I was pumping, I was in an awkward position.

14:07.328 --> 14:10.932
As soon as I got up, I felt immediate pain in my back.

14:10.972 --> 14:13.295
And I thought I would go after a few hours and it didn't go.

14:13.355 --> 14:15.397
And I thought maybe a few days and it still didn't go.

14:16.118 --> 14:26.730
And so after a few months, actually my leg, my left leg started to form numbness all the way to my feet and half my foot all the way up my left leg became numb.

14:27.330 --> 14:31.495
And I saw different treatments and I'm thankful for many who prayed.

14:31.535 --> 14:34.258
And after months, it still remained.

14:34.914 --> 14:37.317
And that constant pain and numbing still remain.

14:37.837 --> 14:41.682
And even till today, that numbing still remains.

14:42.543 --> 14:47.569
I remember sending scans and x-rays to a cousin of mine who's a spinal surgeon.

14:47.629 --> 14:52.855
And one thing he said really struck me, he said, the numbing may never go.

14:54.076 --> 14:55.277
And that hit me very hard.

14:55.338 --> 14:56.959
And that really shocked me.

14:57.140 --> 15:01.485
And I remember just praying and asking God and still haven't experienced.

15:01.505 --> 15:02.706
Now it's gotten much better.

15:03.202 --> 15:06.066
but haven't completely experienced that healing.

15:06.086 --> 15:12.755
And with two young kids, it's often challenging because they want their daddy to lift them and carry them and do lots of activities with them.

15:13.596 --> 15:22.628
But I've come to realize and trust that whether God heals or not, my attitude should remain of trust and belief and joy that God is there.

15:23.389 --> 15:31.119
And whether he chooses to completely heal or not, I will trust and keep that attitude, a positive attitude of trust and faith in him.

15:31.740 --> 15:33.042
And so there are times in life

15:33.474 --> 15:39.261
We may not experience the healing we want or even the time we want.

15:40.102 --> 15:45.328
But God heals us and he chooses through his sovereignty for his purpose and his glory.

15:45.929 --> 15:49.313
Now there are three reasons we see in why healing occurred in Scripture.

15:49.894 --> 15:51.476
One, the first is for his glory.

15:51.956 --> 15:56.161
That his name is magnified and character revealed for others to come to know him.

15:56.181 --> 16:03.410
So God heals for his purpose, for his glory that others would see his power demonstrated through miraculous healings.

16:03.874 --> 16:05.657
that they would know who Jesus Christ is.

16:06.118 --> 16:17.398
Second, for membership, during the ministry of Jesus, many of His mighty healings could be tied to the restoration of the membership of people who were ostracized or cut off from the community because of sickness.

16:17.979 --> 16:24.591
In the Scriptures, we read of people who would not be able to partake of worship and community life because they had illness.

16:24.611 --> 16:26.354
And so when God healed them,

16:26.466 --> 16:32.034
They were now brought back into community and fellowship with the others to be brought into the family of God.

16:32.054 --> 16:38.263
And so healing was not only an inauguration of new creation, it was the welcoming of those who were outside of the community.

16:38.583 --> 16:46.634
Jews and Gentiles alike to bring them as part of the new community and new family, a new kingdom, the kingdom of God and the family of God.

16:47.075 --> 16:52.082
And the third, healing occurs as a foretaste of new creation.

16:52.418 --> 16:59.926
The work of healing is actually a signpost pointing to the way of new creation, when God will heal and restore.

17:00.386 --> 17:05.431
It's an event that happens and occurs in the present that points to a future reality.

17:05.451 --> 17:11.797
So when someone is healed now, it's actually pointing to a time in new creation when there will no be no more sickness.

17:12.218 --> 17:14.260
And God will heal all things.

17:14.280 --> 17:20.306
That's why John writes in Revelation 21, verse three, he says, look, God's dwelling place is now among the people.

17:20.386 --> 17:21.728
and He will dwell with them.

17:22.028 --> 17:31.800
He will wipe away every tear from their eyes and there will be no more death, no more mourning, no more crying or pain for the old order of things have passed away.

17:32.581 --> 17:36.546
One day there will be no more sickness and pain and disease and death.

17:36.566 --> 17:43.254
So not only is healing a signpost, it actually is a little bit of new creation coming to meet us now in the present.

17:43.614 --> 17:46.898
It gives us a foretaste of what reality will be like.

17:47.618 --> 18:05.907
You see, when we're healed, it's not only for the comfort of our own body that we feel relief, but it shows to others, especially people who don't believe in God, of a future reality, a future life where sin and sickness and death will be eliminated, will be no more, we will receive new resurrected bodies.

18:05.927 --> 18:07.068
Now isn't that exciting?

18:08.310 --> 18:13.298
And so as Jehovah Raffa, he heals us to point us to a future reality.

18:14.146 --> 18:17.911
Now God is Rafa throughout the Old Testament can be seen in three distinct ways.

18:18.653 --> 18:23.399
He heals physically, he heals emotionally, and he heals spiritually.

18:24.501 --> 18:33.114
While physical healing is important in this present life, it appears that God's primary purpose or agenda is spiritual healing and emotional healing.

18:33.574 --> 18:39.042
Now it's important to know that the people Jesus physically healed or raised from the dead eventually died.

18:39.763 --> 18:41.746
So whether God decides to heal or not,

18:42.018 --> 18:44.741
It's according to what he sovereignly chooses.

18:45.362 --> 18:51.289
And there have been many godly women and men who have struggled with illness and never saw healing in their bodies.

18:52.130 --> 18:54.833
Such one is a lady named Annie Johnson Flint.

18:55.293 --> 18:59.698
She was born in New Jersey and when her parents died, she was just five years old.

19:00.179 --> 19:06.226
She and her sister lived for two unhappy years with a widow who had two children of her own and was with limited income.

19:06.850 --> 19:13.077
Then a childless couple known as the Flints adopted her and her sister and they deeply loved Jesus and they deeply loved the girls.

19:13.758 --> 19:16.721
And Annie received Jesus as a savior around the age of eight.

19:17.442 --> 19:22.828
She grew up and taught school for three years until severe rheumatoid arthritis made it no longer possible.

19:23.369 --> 19:25.651
And within two additional years she was unable to walk.

19:26.572 --> 19:35.122
She moved to Clifton Springs, New York in hope of finding a cure but instead she had to give up her dreams of being a concert pianist and lived in constant writhing pain.

19:35.330 --> 19:38.013
And she had twisted arms and bodies.

19:38.033 --> 19:42.617
And near the end of her life, cancer started to eat inside of her and her vision was lost.

19:42.637 --> 19:45.200
And she was suffering from incontinence and had to wear diapers.

19:46.421 --> 19:50.204
And Annie sought always to everything with her Lord.

19:50.665 --> 19:55.189
And after nearly 50 years of suffering, she submitted to him.

19:55.590 --> 19:58.913
And her last words were, it's all right.

19:59.974 --> 20:00.595
It's all right.

20:01.796 --> 20:04.178
A life of unanswered questions.

20:04.546 --> 20:05.948
She penned this beautiful hymn.

20:07.009 --> 20:09.632
He giveth more grace when the burdens grow greater.

20:10.112 --> 20:12.535
He sendeth more strength when the labors increase.

20:12.975 --> 20:18.121
To add it affliction, he added his mercy to multiply trials as multiply peace.

20:18.141 --> 20:28.092
When we have exhausted our store of endurance, when our strength has failed, or the day has have done, when we reach the end of our hoard of resources, our father's full giving has only begun.

20:28.353 --> 20:33.138
His love has no limit, his grace has no measure, his power has no boundary known unto men.

20:33.442 --> 20:39.329
For out of his infinite riches in Jesus, he giveth, he giveth, and he giveth again.

20:39.369 --> 20:46.177
And whatever you and I are going through in life, his grace is sufficient and he gives and he gives and he gives.

20:46.917 --> 20:57.510
You see, the reason the early church was willing to face horrific persecution and torture and painful martyrdom is because they knew of their God and they trusted in the promise of resurrection and internal life.

20:58.150 --> 21:01.394
And today, if you're struggling with a physical infirmity or illness,

21:01.538 --> 21:11.894
I want to encourage you to surrender and believe a God that can heal and trust in him, to decide in his sovereignty what's best for you and for me for his glory.

21:12.636 --> 21:18.605
So whether it's complete healing or grace or joy to endure the difficulty in hardships, we are called to trust God.

21:19.326 --> 21:29.202
The Hebrew word in the text for Rafa means to mend as a garment, to amend or repair as a building is reconstructed or to cure as a disease person is restored.

21:29.922 --> 21:40.495
What God was trying to teach them was even though he made the bitter water sweet and that healing was there as they hearkened to his voice and that they would do that which was right in his sight.

21:41.657 --> 21:47.744
But out of all the bitter waters and all what they experienced, God was asking and hoping that they would trust him.

21:49.026 --> 21:55.314
And we can see, but all of us, we have these bitter waters in our lives spiritually.

21:55.714 --> 22:00.461
The waters of our soul have become polluted and contaminated and made bitter due to sin.

22:01.162 --> 22:03.104
And so what is the solution to the bitter waters?

22:03.785 --> 22:04.306
It's a tree.

22:05.528 --> 22:06.649
It's called the cross.

22:07.450 --> 22:18.425
This tree at Mara symbolizes the cross of Jesus Christ at Calvary, which transformed the bitter waters of sin into the sweet waters of God's redemption and healing, deliverance, and eternal life.

22:19.046 --> 22:24.754
Our healing, spiritual, emotional, physical are related to what Jesus accomplished at the cross.

22:25.314 --> 22:30.599
So the tree that Moses threw in the waters and made sweet points to the bitterness of his crucifixion.

22:30.659 --> 22:33.141
It was a horrible event at the cross.

22:33.702 --> 22:35.644
That was a very bitter experience.

22:36.785 --> 22:42.150
Mixed with the bitterness of our human sin has given us the sweetness of God's salvation.

22:42.870 --> 22:47.134
Isaiah 53 verse five reminds us that he was wounded for our transgressions.

22:47.415 --> 22:49.016
He was bruised for our iniquities.

22:49.336 --> 22:55.282
The chastisement for our peace was upon him and by his stripes we

22:55.458 --> 22:56.039
are healed.

22:56.980 --> 23:02.326
I'd like to demonstrate the transforming power, the healing power of God in our lives.

23:02.366 --> 23:04.849
And I have here a demonstration, three cups.

23:06.131 --> 23:10.216
A cup that represents Jesus, us or me, and sin.

23:12.178 --> 23:16.643
And due to sin, when sin entered the world, it fractured our lives.

23:16.804 --> 23:21.850
It caused us to live with this bitterness of soul.

23:21.990 --> 23:25.394
And so I'm going to put this liquid here, and you can see now

23:25.538 --> 23:27.961
that sin has infected our lives.

23:28.842 --> 23:32.746
But through the cross is Moses cast that tree into the waters.

23:33.146 --> 23:55.090
And even as Jesus died and the cross of Jesus has made a way for us to experience healing and cleansing and forgiveness and deliverance and healing and eternal life and the promise of resurrection, we see here Jesus now comes into our lives when we invite him into our lives and he's able to make that bitter water to disappear.

23:55.426 --> 23:57.749
to make us clean, to make us whole.

23:58.429 --> 24:20.413
And the amazing thing is through the power of Jesus that sin, one day will be destroyed and sin has no power over God because God has destroyed the work of sin and one day as we've read he will eliminate all sin, sickness, disease, death, all the power of evil, every work of the enemy will be destroyed ultimately and eradicated because of the power of God.

24:20.453 --> 24:24.658
And so when sin tries to

24:25.410 --> 24:26.774
affect who God is.

24:26.834 --> 24:35.561
It doesn't affect who God is because God has now destroyed the work of sin and the power of sin and sin will ultimately be no more.

24:35.942 --> 24:37.266
How many are thankful this morning?

24:38.018 --> 24:43.645
for the power of Jesus, for the power of his blood, for the power of resurrection that gives us healing and life.

24:43.885 --> 24:46.328
You see, the cross heals us from the sickness of sin.

24:46.609 --> 24:51.034
The cross heals us from the diseases of pride and lust and greed and hate and prejudice.

24:51.054 --> 24:56.881
The cross heals us from the disease of idolatry and hatred and contention and selfish ambition and jealousies.

24:57.141 --> 25:00.926
The cross heals us from the diseases of sexual sins and murders and divisions.

25:01.226 --> 25:04.210
The cross heals us from the guilt that is produced by sin.

25:04.354 --> 25:07.757
The cross can heal a broken in heart and bind up our wounds.

25:08.037 --> 25:12.562
The cross can give recovery of sight both physically and those who become blinded by sin.

25:13.222 --> 25:17.687
The cross invites us to repent of our sins and can heal even this nation.

25:18.167 --> 25:24.613
You see, the biggest problem we have in our society today and the root of all of our problems is the problem of sin.

25:25.314 --> 25:29.858
And we can drink from sin, but it is bitter water to our tastes and ultimately leads to death.

25:30.379 --> 25:34.002
Jesus told the woman at the well in John 4, verse 13 into 14,

25:34.082 --> 25:37.286
Whoever drinks of this water will thirst again, that bitter water.

25:37.766 --> 25:46.676
Whoever drinks from the water that I will give will never thirst again, for out of them will flow waters of eternal or everlasting life.

25:47.336 --> 25:49.919
You know, we heard last week about God being Shalom.

25:50.320 --> 25:54.644
Shalom means peace, but the deeper meaning of peace is completeness and wholeness.

25:55.265 --> 25:59.730
You see, when sin entered the world, it fractured our relationship with God.

25:59.874 --> 26:02.457
It fractured the relationship between heaven and earth.

26:02.797 --> 26:08.183
It fractured our relationship with each other and it fractured who we are as humanity, as humans.

26:08.744 --> 26:17.433
And through the cross, Jesus wants to bring Shalom and wholeness back to the world, back to us, back to our relationships.

26:17.493 --> 26:25.202
God as our healers working through a process of putting the pieces of life back together, pointing towards wholeness and peace.

26:25.570 --> 26:32.139
And he wants to bring the fragmentation in our lives and in our marriages, in our relationships, and in creation together.

26:32.199 --> 26:37.306
And maybe there's some sin in our lives that has fragmented our minds and our hearts.

26:37.707 --> 26:41.712
And God is here as our healer to bring us to Shalom.

26:41.732 --> 26:43.254
Now healing is often a process.

26:43.535 --> 26:46.559
Now God can instantly heal, but most often it's a process.

26:47.039 --> 26:50.544
God can also use various methods and people to bring about healing.

26:50.805 --> 26:54.770
He can use doctors and medicines as instruments to bring physical healing.

26:54.946 --> 27:03.287
He can use people such as pastors, counselors, therapists, and help us to help us bring spiritual or emotional healing through counseling, spiritual direction, and prayer.

27:04.029 --> 27:07.698
You see, the purpose of God being Rafa is to bring us to Shalom.

27:08.386 --> 27:11.010
The Lord can bring healing to every aspect of our life.

27:11.030 --> 27:12.273
He can heal us emotionally.

27:12.533 --> 27:15.839
He can heal a person who has bitterness and envy and pride.

27:16.059 --> 27:18.543
He can deliver a person from anger and unforgiveness.

27:18.563 --> 27:19.605
He can heal our stress.

27:19.645 --> 27:23.572
He can heal and deliver us from the spiritual bondages and demonic forces.

27:23.932 --> 27:26.477
He can bring healing to our relationships and our marriages.

27:26.517 --> 27:27.518
He can heal your mind.

27:27.759 --> 27:30.744
He can heal your body and he can heal our land.

27:30.844 --> 27:32.146
How many can say amen today?

27:33.428 --> 27:34.450
Now sometime,

27:35.458 --> 27:50.116
take some time quietly, even today or even through this week, and allow the Holy Spirit to search our hearts and our minds and our motives and our actions and our emotions, and see if there is any wicked way or bitter water within us.

27:51.117 --> 27:55.723
As Assamas, to search me of God and know my way and see if there be any evil way in me.

27:56.644 --> 28:04.754
If he brings anything to our minds, confess and repent and begin to walk in obedience to God's Word and allow him to turn the bitter waters

28:04.898 --> 28:06.941
to pure sweet waters.

28:08.203 --> 28:14.492
So how can we get to this place that we can walk and allow Jehovah Rafa to bring us to a place of Shalom?

28:14.512 --> 28:16.094
There are two words I like to leave us with.

28:16.194 --> 28:18.157
It's found in Psalm 37 verse 5.

28:18.758 --> 28:24.567
It says, commit your ways to the Lord and trust also in Him and He will bring it to pass.

28:25.187 --> 28:27.351
Two words in specific order, commit.

28:28.032 --> 28:29.714
This is an act required of us.

28:30.242 --> 28:32.506
You see, we often say, my way is my way of life.

28:32.586 --> 28:35.351
I do certain things my way and I want to do it my way.

28:36.473 --> 28:37.815
Because I believe this is the right way.

28:38.336 --> 28:41.702
But what God is asking us is to commit our ways to Him.

28:42.283 --> 28:45.869
It's an active surrender of doing things the way God wants us.

28:45.909 --> 28:55.986
And so this morning, will you commit or surrender your life, your circumstance, your body, your sickness, your emotions, your heart, your mind to God?

28:56.418 --> 29:00.002
And the second, trust also in him and he will bring it to pass.

29:00.022 --> 29:02.745
This is an attitude, a genuine commitment.

29:03.366 --> 29:06.289
I've committed my ways to the Lord and I trust him.

29:06.729 --> 29:08.771
Now think about your bank account.

29:08.791 --> 29:21.525
Once we commit our money to the bank to be deposited, when you deposit your money or whether it's electronically or when you physically go to a bank and deposit money, you don't worry at night whether the money is in the account.

29:22.406 --> 29:25.970
You've committed it and you trust and you rest.

29:26.722 --> 29:29.025
And this morning, God wants us to know him as our healer.

29:29.625 --> 29:37.234
And this will require a commitment to trust him, to surrender because he knows what we need more than we do.

29:38.295 --> 29:40.898
Surely he can heal our physical ailments if he chooses.

29:41.619 --> 29:50.329
But the primary purpose of this text that God is pointing towards is that we would walk in his ways, not in the ways of the world that leads to a sin six soul.

29:50.369 --> 29:55.154
And when our sin six soul is all messed up,

29:55.714 --> 29:59.598
It causes our minds to be messed up, our emotional life, far from being healthy.

30:00.159 --> 30:01.360
We become fragmented.

30:02.001 --> 30:03.382
And so God is asking us to commit.

30:03.422 --> 30:06.326
Remember what Jesus did on the cross in that agonizing moment?

30:06.606 --> 30:15.976
He prayed then ultimately the last words, when he was experiencing pain and separation and death, he said, Father, into your hands, I commit my soul.

30:16.056 --> 30:17.017
I commit my life.

30:17.938 --> 30:20.141
And then there's an aspect of trust and rest.

30:20.541 --> 30:21.703
Trust God with your body.

30:22.043 --> 30:23.224
Trust God with your heart.

30:23.525 --> 30:24.786
Trust God with your mind.

30:24.866 --> 30:26.809
and trust God with your soul.

30:27.971 --> 30:34.341
You see, if God chooses to heal your body and allow you to experience a little glimpse of new creation, then praise God for it.

30:35.723 --> 30:48.343
Like we've witnessed and we've heard the miraculous healing story of Kevin and Shaqeena's beautiful twins, a remarkable healing story of God miraculously intervening when there seemed to be no hope and death was certain.

30:48.964 --> 30:50.066
God intervened

30:50.242 --> 30:57.872
through so many means, through the medical means, through prayer, through his divine intervention to bring about a miraculous healing.

30:58.813 --> 31:05.561
But also realize that through his spirit, he wants to heal the fragmentation in our minds due to the lies of the enemy.

31:06.242 --> 31:10.728
He wants to heal the fragmentation in our hearts and our relationships and our emotions.

31:10.748 --> 31:15.093
You've seen sinned fragments and God wants to bring us to a wholeness.

31:16.134 --> 31:19.058
As I close this morning, I'd like to share a story

31:19.714 --> 31:21.217
about our own family.

31:21.417 --> 31:23.701
It was the summer of 1993, 30 years ago.

31:23.961 --> 31:28.649
As a family, we traveled to Australia to visit a lot of our immediate family there.

31:29.590 --> 31:41.310
And during the trip, the Lord was speaking to my dad about a calling and a purpose for his life, but he shared after how there was a time that God was inviting him to do something there and active obedience, but he held back and he didn't do it.

31:42.192 --> 31:46.098
And so when he came back, within a few weeks after returning,

31:46.338 --> 31:54.089
Sunday he started to notice that he was losing vision in his right eye and he went and he found that ultimately he lost complete vision in his right eye.

31:54.109 --> 32:00.158
His central vein had collapsed and he went from doctor to doctor specialist specialist and all of them said there's nothing you can do.

32:00.718 --> 32:06.627
Most likely you're going to lose sight in the other eye and if your eyes like this who knows what else is wrong within your body.

32:07.889 --> 32:12.275
And so he prayed and he realized there was no medical intervention possible for this.

32:12.295 --> 32:14.418
He prayed and he was just seeking God and one night

32:14.754 --> 32:18.759
The Lord visited him and gave them the song of their very old songs that, oh, he touched me.

32:19.179 --> 32:20.681
Oh, the joy that floods my soul.

32:21.261 --> 32:24.525
Something happened and now I know he touched me and he made me whole.

32:25.386 --> 32:28.410
So when he woke up with that song, he called everyone and said, oh, God, God healed him.

32:28.530 --> 32:34.657
And he believed God was, you know, healed him from his illness and from the inability to see with his right eye.

32:35.598 --> 32:37.040
But still nothing happened.

32:37.380 --> 32:42.706
Later on, he came to realize what God was beginning was a work of emotional and spiritual healing in his life.

32:43.810 --> 32:46.773
And then November 1, 1993, he invited a pastor.

32:46.873 --> 32:49.115
He was visiting and he was just sharing from the scriptures.

32:49.816 --> 32:57.243
And that evening, God divinely came and a divine visitation for my entire family and brother and I and my mom and dad.

32:57.604 --> 32:59.866
We were there in a supernatural encounter.

32:59.886 --> 33:01.207
We all experienced God.

33:01.888 --> 33:11.858
And I believe on that day forward, God was working in all of our lives and particularly my dad's life where he experienced that spiritual healing that ultimately within a few

33:12.034 --> 33:15.318
months without even him realizing he could see again.

33:15.599 --> 33:17.141
And his eye was completely healed.

33:17.361 --> 33:18.543
It was a miraculous healing.

33:19.444 --> 33:29.137
And it's interesting the year later in 94, we went out to England and to visit family and his brother, who's a doctor, wanted to check and see, he couldn't believe what happened to his eye.

33:29.157 --> 33:35.586
And he checked his eye and he actually found that the eye that was damaged and healed was actually better than his other eye.

33:36.427 --> 33:37.008
Praise God.

33:37.729 --> 33:38.610
God can heal.

33:39.426 --> 33:49.297
But he also not only heals physically, but he wants to do a work of healing spiritually, emotionally in our hearts, in our lives, to draw us to him and to his purpose.

33:50.138 --> 33:54.883
And so this morning, do you believe that God is your healer?

33:56.905 --> 33:59.368
That he's here today to heal you.

34:00.029 --> 34:03.613
That he is here to heal your heart, your mind, and your body.

34:04.234 --> 34:05.755
And so will you commit to him?

34:06.576 --> 34:07.317
And will you trust?

34:07.357 --> 34:08.178
And will you say,

34:08.674 --> 34:11.000
I believe, Lord, you're my healer.

34:11.943 --> 34:14.309
We all have things in our lives we need healing from.

34:15.211 --> 34:16.836
We have relationships we need healing.

34:17.417 --> 34:22.290
We have in our mind and our heart because sin pervades our whole society in our lives.

34:22.466 --> 34:38.848
It encounters the enemy constantly comes to bring lies into our minds, to doubt God's love, to doubt God's purpose, to bring confusion and misunderstanding in our lives, to hold us in bitterness and captivity based on what maybe someone has done to us or what may be occurring in our lives or the lives we believe.

34:39.309 --> 34:45.878
But God wants to bring healing this morning to you and to me if you will receive it.

34:45.898 --> 34:51.666
And so if you would join with me in saying this prayer that's on the screen and verbalize it together,

34:52.066 --> 34:53.589
Would you join with me as we pray?

34:55.813 --> 35:00.182
Loving Father, touch me now with your healing hands.

35:01.324 --> 35:07.316
May your will be done in my mind, body, soul, and spirit.

35:08.298 --> 35:10.963
I commit my life to you and trust you.

35:11.945 --> 35:14.290
In Jesus' name, amen.

